# Corp Web Design Alignment (TMaaS)

Marketing pages (`/`, `/marketplace`, `/service/:id`) share the **DQ corp web design system** from `DQ_CORPWEB_PROTOTYPE`. They must **not** mirror the corp homepage section stack or copy patterns.

## Copy punctuation
- Do not use em dashes (`‚Äî`) in user-facing copy, meta tags, or email templates. Use commas, colons, periods, or a regular hyphen (`-`) instead.

## Share with corp web (design system)
- Body font: **Plus Jakarta Sans** (`font-sans`), not Inter
- Brand colors: `text-dq-navy` (#030F35), `text-dq-orange` (#FB5535)
- Headings: `font-semibold`, not `font-bold`; hero up to `lg:text-8xl`
- Eyebrow labels: `font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-dq-orange`
- Section padding: `py-24 px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-10`
- Content max-width: `max-w-[1200px] mx-auto` (heroes may use `max-w-7xl`)
- Alternate backgrounds: `white` / `bg-gray-50`
- Navbar: static `sticky top-0 h-16`, no scroll-morph pill effect
- Cards: `rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 hover:border-dq-orange hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300`
- CTAs: `rounded-full`; primary orange on product landing (`btnPrimary` ‚Üí `dq-cta-primary` + `bg-[#FB5535]`); secondary glass (`bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm border`)
- Hero backgrounds: `MeshSection` with `hero-grid` overlay and mesh CSS vars from `index.css`
- Footer section labels: `font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gray-400`
- Footer link columns: **Explore** (Marketplace, Talk to our team, flag-gated), **Follow Us** (LinkedIn, X, YouTube, Explore DigitalQatalyst external link). No separate DQ column.
- Footer bottom bar: Privacy and Terms always link in-app to `/legal/privacy` and `/legal/terms` (MVP). The `legal` flag gates only the `/legal` hub and `/legal/faq`.
- Footer and hero descriptions use `PLATFORM_NAME_EXPANDED` / expanded copy: **Transformation Management as a Service (TMaaS)** via `brandLinks.ts`
- Service count copy is **100+** everywhere (not 50+ or 200+); typical start time is **<1 day** (not 4 wks)
- Corp web links use `https://www.digitalqatalyst.com` base URL; TMaaS product link label is **Marketplace** (not "Design & Deploy Services")
- Platform display name is **Marketplace** (`PLATFORM_NAME`, `PLATFORM_ACRONYM`, and `PLATFORM_BRAND_LINE` in `src/lib/brandLinks.ts`). Do not revert to "Transformation as a Service", "TMaaS", "Transformation Management as a Service", or "Technology Management as a Service" as the platform name.

## Differentiate for product pages (TMaaS landing)
- Use **product landing IA** per `specs/landing-page-prototype-shell.md` v2, default at `/` (`IndexProductLanding`, `src/components/site/landing/v2/`)
- v1 corp-mirror alternate landing at `/landing-v1` (`IndexTraditional`); `/landing-v2` redirects to `/`
- Hero: TMaaS logo, marketplace mockup; orange primary CTA ‚Üí `/marketplace` (no product badge row)
- Landing navbar: Services nav link stays grey on all routes (no orange active state)
- One dark mesh narrative section (`Why TMaaS`); do not alternate dark sections like corp homepage
- Do **not** add corp-only sections: Team, FAQ, Framework, full ecosystem product grid
- Do **not** copy corp homepage stats, problem copy, or section order verbatim
- Parent brand: optional `Part of DigitalQatalyst` external link; full corp credibility stays on corp web

## Product landing copy (TMaaS positioning)
- **Marketing + SEO first**: plain language, short sentences, searchable terms (`digital transformation`, `marketplace`, `services`, `blueprints`, `AI-powered`)
- Avoid internal jargon on the landing page: `industrialise`, `productised`, `governed fulfilment`, `operating platform`, `architecture-led`
- Hero H1 should include **digital transformation**; subcopy mirrors USP in one or two short sentences (low-cost marketplace, AI-powered blueprints, transparent pricing, weeks not months)
- Problem cards: three short pains (slow, expensive, hard to adapt); closing line ties to marketplace + blueprints
- Outcome cards: cost, speed, scale with substantiated metrics only (`<1 day`, `100+`, `From $1k`)
- Journey steps: Discover (browse) ‚Üí Evaluate (compare) ‚Üí Engage (launch with team)
- Primary CTA: **Browse services**; secondary: **Talk to our team**
- Badge row: `TMaaS` + status chip (e.g. Live); page `<title>` and meta description use TMaaS + digital transformation marketplace keywords

## Marketing page copy (Marketplace, Service Detail, Contact)
- Same voice as homepage: plain language, short sentences, SEO terms (`digital transformation`, `marketplace`, `services`, `blueprints`)
- Shared CTA labels: **Browse marketplace** (secondary on landing), **Schedule free advisory** (primary conversion for launch offer in navbar, hero, closing CTA, marketplace launch band); **Talk to our team** remains on footer and service-detail flows; avoid "Explore Marketplace", "Contact Us", "Book a Consultation"
- Launch offer: free transformation advisory via `src/lib/launchOffering.ts` ‚Üí `/contact?offering=launch-advisory`; marketplace `MarketplaceLaunchOffer` is a single CTA card (ctaOrange mesh + grid, not a service card) below the featured carousel; catalog section uses `pt-10 md:pt-12` below hero
- Landing hero H1: use `landingHeroHeading` from `brandAccent.ts` (`dq-landing-hero-heading` class in `globals.css`, corp scale 2.75rem ‚Üí 6rem); two-line split with second line `text-dq-orange`
- Primary orange fills: `btnPrimary` uses `dq-cta-primary` + `bg-[#FB5535]` (literal hex, no `transition-colors` on `<a>`); `a.dq-cta-primary` anchor rule in `globals.css` for Chrome/macOS
- Marketplace hero: eyebrow `Digital transformation marketplace`; H1 `Browse transformation services` with **transformation** in `text-dq-orange`; use `landingHeroHeading` scale and tall hero padding (`lg:pb-24 lg:pt-28`, min-height ~360px on desktop)
- Marketplace featured carousel: eyebrow `Curated selection`; H2 `Featured services` (not "Top picks")
- Contact hero: H1 `Tell us what you need. We'll help you get started.`; submit button `Send request`
- Service detail bottom CTA: `Not sure if this is the right fit?` + **Talk to our team** / **Browse more services**
- Package card CTAs by stage: Assess and Design **Get started**, Deploy **Get a quote**, Managed **Talk to our team**, Bundle **Request proposal** (`getServicePackageCta` in `contactFormPrefill.ts`)
- Set `document.title` per page: Marketplace, Contact, and each Service Detail include `TMaaS` and searchable terms

