## Responsive layout (marketing pages)
- Prevent page-level horizontal scroll: `overflow-x: clip` on `html`/`body`; clip decorative overflow on hero mockup wrappers (`overflow-hidden` + inner padding, 3D transform only from `lg:`)
- Hero mockup (`HeroDashboardMockup`): no box-shadow, drop-shadow, or glow behind the card ‚Äî border only on the white frame
- Sticky navbar clearance: hero sections use `pt-20 md:pt-24` (or `pt-16 md:pt-24` on landing hero), not `pt-14`
- Hero H1 scale: stepped down on narrow viewports; two-column heroes use `lg:text-7xl xl:text-8xl`, not `lg:text-8xl` in a split grid
- Horizontal tab/category nav: `flex-nowrap overflow-x-auto scrollbar-none`; tab triggers `shrink-0`
- Marketplace catalog toolbar: stack on mobile (`flex-col` ‚Üí `sm:flex-row`); sort + view controls `w-full sm:w-auto`
- Best-sellers carousel: header row + nav buttons in one flex row inside `<Carousel>` (buttons need carousel context)
- Service detail delivery stepper: vertical timeline below `lg`; horizontal grid uses `grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4` for four steps
- CTAs on mobile: primary actions `w-full sm:w-auto` in stacked CTA rows (landing, contact, service detail bottom band)
- Contact form: submit button full width on mobile; consent label must not use `whitespace-nowrap`

## Contact form Turnstile
- Production requires `VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY` and `TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY` (Cloudflare Turnstile)
- Local dev: `.env.example` documents always-pass test keys; `ContactTurnstile` and `contact-security.js` fall back to test keys when unset in dev
- Do not block form submission in dev solely because Turnstile env vars are missing

